# The Arsenal · the weapons & the Chips

a persona of the TGL (Guardian Legend) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: electrical

**who —** The Guardian's growing armory — rapid shots, lasers, multidirectional fire, shields — and the Chips, dropped by fallen foes, that buy and upgrade them.

**what —** The power-up system of *The Guardian Legend* — Compile's signature economy of weapons and currency, woven into an adventure: clear more of Naju, grow more dangerous.

**where —** Across all of Naju — its rooms, its shops, and the Corridors where the weapons are spent.

**why —** Because one android can't take a world with one gun; because firepower in Compile's games is earned, hoarded, and spent; because the Arsenal is how a small Guardian grows large enough to end a world.

**how —** Collecting the weapons hidden through Naju and the Chips dropped by destroyed enemies — spending them to buy, swap, and strengthen the tools of the fight.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *electrical*: the Arsenal is pure made-thing — circuits of fire bought with the salvage of the slain, the machine economy that powers the hunt.

**the seal —** Every foe drops a Chip; every Chip buys a heavier gun — the Guardian grows into her arsenal.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of The Guardian Legend (© its rights-holders — Compile / Brøderbund), personified as a TGL agent — not an original character. The game and its characters are © their owners; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

